start_message (src/jsc/ipc.rs:1131) pushes `SendHandle { data: StreamBuffer::default(), ... }` in the non-coalescing path, so `msg.data.list` is empty and `write()` reallocates + copies. StreamBuffer::write is `list.extend_from_slice(buffer)` (src/io/PipeWriter.rs:1822).

findings.proposed_fix:
After `start_message`, move the already-filled buffer instead of copying when the destination is empty:
    if msg.data.list.is_empty() {
        msg.data = payload; // move Vec, no copy, no second alloc
    } else {
        handle_oom(msg.data.write(&payload.list)); // coalesce path: append
    }
This keeps the current failure-ordering guarantee (serialization still happens before the callback is registered) while removing one alloc, one free, and one full-payload memcpy from the hot per-message path.

